33// Setup for Windows DLL export/import. When building the V8 DLL the
34// BUILDING_V8_SHARED needs to be defined. When building a program which uses
35// the V8 DLL USING_V8_SHARED needs to be defined. When either building the V8
36// static library or building a program which uses the V8 static library neither
37// BUILDING_V8_SHARED nor USING_V8_SHARED should be defined.
38#ifdef BUILDING_V8_SHARED
39# define V8_EXPORT __declspec(dllexport)
40#elif USING_V8_SHARED
41# define V8_EXPORT __declspec(dllimport)
42#else
43# define V8_EXPORT
44#endif // BUILDING_V8_SHARED
45
46#else // V8_OS_WIN

49#if V8_HAS_ATTRIBUTE_VISIBILITY
50# ifdef BUILDING_V8_SHARED
51# define V8_EXPORT __attribute__ ((visibility("default")))
52# else
53# define V8_EXPORT
54# endif
55#else
56# define V8_EXPORT
57#endif
58
59#endif // V8_OS_WIN

165const int kApiPointerSize = sizeof(void*); // NOLINT
166const int kApiDoubleSize = sizeof(double); // NOLINT
167const int kApiIntSize = sizeof(int); // NOLINT
168const int kApiInt64Size = sizeof(int64_t); // NOLINT
169
170// Tag information for HeapObject.
171const int kHeapObjectTag = 1;
172const int kWeakHeapObjectTag = 3;
173const int kHeapObjectTagSize = 2;
174const intptr_t kHeapObjectTagMask = (1 << kHeapObjectTagSize) - 1;
175
176// Tag information for Smi.
177const int kSmiTag = 0;
178const int kSmiTagSize = 1;
179const intptr_t kSmiTagMask = (1 << kSmiTagSize) - 1;
180
181template <size_t tagged_ptr_size>
182struct SmiTagging;
183
184template <int kSmiShiftSize>
185V8_INLINE internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
186 int smi_shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
187 intptr_t tagged_value =
188 (static_cast<intptr_t>(value) << smi_shift_bits) | kSmiTag;
189 return reinterpret_cast<internal::Object*>(tagged_value);
190}
191
192// Smi constants for systems where tagged pointer is a 32-bit value.
193template <>
194struct SmiTagging<4> {
195 enum { kSmiShiftSize = 0, kSmiValueSize = 31 };
196 static int SmiShiftSize() { return kSmiShiftSize; }
197 static int SmiValueSize() { return kSmiValueSize; }
198 V8_INLINE static int SmiToInt(const internal::Object* value) {
199 int shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
200 // Throw away top 32 bits and shift down (requires >> to be sign extending).
201 return static_cast<int>(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(value)) >> shift_bits;
202 }
203 V8_INLINE static internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
204 return internal::IntToSmi<kSmiShiftSize>(value);
205 }
206 V8_INLINE static bool IsValidSmi(intptr_t value) {
207 // To be representable as an tagged small integer, the two
208 // most-significant bits of 'value' must be either 00 or 11 due to
209 // sign-extension. To check this we add 01 to the two
210 // most-significant bits, and check if the most-significant bit is 0
211 //
212 // CAUTION: The original code below:
213 // bool result = ((value + 0x40000000) & 0x80000000) == 0;
214 // may lead to incorrect results according to the C language spec, and
215 // in fact doesn't work correctly with gcc4.1.1 in some cases: The
216 // compiler may produce undefined results in case of signed integer
217 // overflow. The computation must be done w/ unsigned ints.
218 return static_cast<uintptr_t>(value) + 0x40000000U < 0x80000000U;
219 }
220};
221
222// Smi constants for systems where tagged pointer is a 64-bit value.
223template <>
224struct SmiTagging<8> {
225 enum { kSmiShiftSize = 31, kSmiValueSize = 32 };
226 static int SmiShiftSize() { return kSmiShiftSize; }
227 static int SmiValueSize() { return kSmiValueSize; }
228 V8_INLINE static int SmiToInt(const internal::Object* value) {
229 int shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
230 // Shift down and throw away top 32 bits.
231 return static_cast<int>(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(value) >> shift_bits);
232 }
233 V8_INLINE static internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
234 return internal::IntToSmi<kSmiShiftSize>(value);
235 }
236 V8_INLINE static bool IsValidSmi(intptr_t value) {
237 // To be representable as a long smi, the value must be a 32-bit integer.
238 return (value == static_cast<int32_t>(value));
239 }
240};
241
242#if V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
243static_assert(
244 kApiPointerSize == kApiInt64Size,
245 "Pointer compression can be enabled only for 64-bit architectures");
246typedef SmiTagging<4> PlatformSmiTagging;
247#else
248typedef SmiTagging<kApiPointerSize> PlatformSmiTagging;
249#endif
250
251const int kSmiShiftSize = PlatformSmiTagging::kSmiShiftSize;
252const int kSmiValueSize = PlatformSmiTagging::kSmiValueSize;
253const int kSmiMinValue = (static_cast<unsigned int>(-1)) << (kSmiValueSize - 1);
254const int kSmiMaxValue = -(kSmiMinValue + 1);
255constexpr bool SmiValuesAre31Bits() { return kSmiValueSize == 31; }
256constexpr bool SmiValuesAre32Bits() { return kSmiValueSize == 32; }

266#define TYPE_CHECK(T, S) \
267 while (false) { \
268 *(static_cast<T* volatile*>(0)) = static_cast<S*>(0); \
269 }

302template <class T>
303class Local {
304 public:
305 V8_INLINE Local() : val_(0) {}
306 template <class S>
307 V8_INLINE Local(Local<S> that)
308 : val_(reinterpret_cast<T*>(*that)) {
314 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
315 }
316
320 V8_INLINE bool IsEmpty() const { return val_ == 0; }
321
325 V8_INLINE void Clear() { val_ = 0; }
326
327 V8_INLINE T* operator->() const { return val_; }
328
329 V8_INLINE T* operator*() const { return val_; }
330
337 template <class S>
338 V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Local<S>& that) const {
339 internal::Object** a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_);
340 internal::Object** b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(that.val_);
341 if (a == 0) return b == 0;
342 if (b == 0) return false;
343 return *a == *b;
344 }
345
346 template <class S> V8_INLINE bool operator==(
347 const PersistentBase<S>& that) const {
348 internal::Object** a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_);
349 internal::Object** b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(that.val_);
350 if (a == 0) return b == 0;
351 if (b == 0) return false;
352 return *a == *b;
353 }
354
361 template <class S>
362 V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Local<S>& that) const {
363 return !operator==(that);
364 }
365
366 template <class S> V8_INLINE bool operator!=(
367 const Persistent<S>& that) const {
368 return !operator==(that);
369 }
370
376 template <class S> V8_INLINE static Local<T> Cast(Local<S> that) {
377#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
378 // If we're going to perform the type check then we have to check
379 // that the handle isn't empty before doing the checked cast.
380 if (that.IsEmpty()) return Local<T>();
381#endif
382 return Local<T>(T::Cast(*that));
383 }
384
390 template <class S>
391 V8_INLINE Local<S> As() const {
392 return Local<S>::Cast(*this);
393 }
394
400 V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate, Local<T> that);
401 V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate,
402 const PersistentBase<T>& that);
403
404 private:
405 friend class Utils;
406 template<class F> friend class Eternal;
407 template<class F> friend class PersistentBase;
408 template<class F, class M> friend class Persistent;
409 template<class F> friend class Local;
410 template <class F>
411 friend class MaybeLocal;
412 template<class F> friend class FunctionCallbackInfo;
413 template<class F> friend class PropertyCallbackInfo;
414 friend class String;
415 friend class Object;
416 friend class Context;
417 friend class Isolate;
418 friend class Private;
419 template<class F> friend class internal::CustomArguments;
420 friend Local<Primitive> Undefined(Isolate* isolate);
421 friend Local<Primitive> Null(Isolate* isolate);
422 friend Local<Boolean> True(Isolate* isolate);
423 friend Local<Boolean> False(Isolate* isolate);
424 friend class HandleScope;
425 friend class EscapableHandleScope;
426 template <class F1, class F2, class F3>
427 friend class PersistentValueMapBase;
428 template<class F1, class F2> friend class PersistentValueVector;
429 template <class F>
430 friend class ReturnValue;
431
432 explicit V8_INLINE Local(T* that) : val_(that) {}
433 V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate, T* that);
434 T* val_;
435};

456class MaybeLocal {

459 template <class S>
460 V8_INLINE MaybeLocal(Local<S> that)
461 : val_(reinterpret_cast<T*>(*that)) {
462 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
463 }
464
465 V8_INLINE bool IsEmpty() const { return val_ == nullptr; }
466
471 template <class S>
472 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT V8_INLINE bool ToLocal(Local<S>* out) const {
473 out->val_ = IsEmpty() ? nullptr : this->val_;
474 return !IsEmpty();
475 }
476
481 V8_INLINE Local<T> ToLocalChecked();
482
487 template <class S>
488 V8_INLINE Local<S> FromMaybe(Local<S> default_value) const {
489 return IsEmpty() ? default_value : Local<S>(val_);
490 }
491
492 private:
493 T* val_;
494};

517static const int kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback = 2;
518static const int kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback = 2;
519
520template <typename T>
521class WeakCallbackInfo {
522 public:
523 typedef void (*Callback)(const WeakCallbackInfo<T>& data);
524
525 WeakCallbackInfo(Isolate* isolate, T* parameter,
526 void* embedder_fields[kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback],
527 Callback* callback)
528 : isolate_(isolate), parameter_(parameter), callback_(callback) {
529 for (int i = 0; i < kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback; ++i) {
530 embedder_fields_[i] = embedder_fields[i];
531 }
532 }
533
534 V8_INLINE Isolate* GetIsolate() const { return isolate_; }
535 V8_INLINE T* GetParameter() const { return parameter_; }
536 V8_INLINE void* GetInternalField(int index) const;
537
538 // When first called, the embedder MUST Reset() the Global which triggered the
539 // callback. The Global itself is unusable for anything else. No v8 other api
540 // calls may be called in the first callback. Should additional work be
541 // required, the embedder must set a second pass callback, which will be
542 // called after all the initial callbacks are processed.
543 // Calling SetSecondPassCallback on the second pass will immediately crash.
544 void SetSecondPassCallback(Callback callback) const { *callback_ = callback; }
545
546 private:
547 Isolate* isolate_;
548 T* parameter_;
549 Callback* callback_;
550 void* embedder_fields_[kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback];
551};
552
553
554// kParameter will pass a void* parameter back to the callback, kInternalFields
555// will pass the first two internal fields back to the callback, kFinalizer
556// will pass a void* parameter back, but is invoked before the object is
557// actually collected, so it can be resurrected. In the last case, it is not
558// possible to request a second pass callback.
559enum class WeakCallbackType { kParameter, kInternalFields, kFinalizer };

574template <class T> class PersistentBase {
575 public:

593 V8_INLINE void Reset(Isolate* isolate, const PersistentBase<S>& other);

595 V8_INLINE bool IsEmpty() const { return val_ == NULL; }
596 V8_INLINE void Empty() { val_ = 0; }
597
598 V8_INLINE Local<T> Get(Isolate* isolate) const {
599 return Local<T>::New(isolate, *this);
600 }
601
602 template <class S>
603 V8_INLINE bool operator==(const PersistentBase<S>& that) const {
604 internal::Object** a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_);
605 internal::Object** b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(that.val_);
606 if (a == NULL) return b == NULL;
607 if (b == NULL) return false;
608 return *a == *b;
609 }
610
611 template <class S>
612 V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Local<S>& that) const {
613 internal::Object** a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_);
614 internal::Object** b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(that.val_);
615 if (a == NULL) return b == NULL;
616 if (b == NULL) return false;
617 return *a == *b;
618 }
619
620 template <class S>
621 V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const PersistentBase<S>& that) const {
622 return !operator==(that);
623 }
624
625 template <class S>
626 V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Local<S>& that) const {

652 V8_INLINE P* ClearWeak();

671
678 V8_DEPRECATE_SOON(
679 "Objects are always considered independent. "
680 "Use MarkActive to avoid collecting otherwise dead weak handles.",

682
690 V8_INLINE void MarkActive();

723 template<class F> friend class PersistentBase;

726 friend class PersistentValueMapBase;
727 template<class F1, class F2> friend class PersistentValueVector;
728 friend class Object;
729
730 explicit V8_INLINE PersistentBase(T* val) : val_(val) {}
731 V8_INLINE static T* New(Isolate* isolate, T* that);
732
733 T* val_;
734};

784template <class T, class M> class Persistent : public PersistentBase<T> {
785 public:
789 V8_INLINE Persistent() : PersistentBase<T>(0) { }
795 template <class S>
796 V8_INLINE Persistent(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> that)
797 : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
798 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
799 }
805 template <class S, class M2>
806 V8_INLINE Persistent(Isolate* isolate, const Persistent<S, M2>& that)
807 : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
808 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
809 }
816 V8_INLINE Persistent(const Persistent& that) : PersistentBase<T>(0) {
817 Copy(that);
818 }
819 template <class S, class M2>
820 V8_INLINE Persistent(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) : PersistentBase<T>(0) {
821 Copy(that);
822 }
823 V8_INLINE Persistent& operator=(const Persistent& that) { // NOLINT
824 Copy(that);
825 return *this;
826 }
827 template <class S, class M2>
828 V8_INLINE Persistent& operator=(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) { // NOLINT
829 Copy(that);
830 return *this;
831 }
837 V8_INLINE ~Persistent() {
838 if (M::kResetInDestructor) this->Reset();
839 }
840
841 // TODO(dcarney): this is pretty useless, fix or remove
842 template <class S>
843 V8_INLINE static Persistent<T>& Cast(const Persistent<S>& that) { // NOLINT
844#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
845 // If we're going to perform the type check then we have to check
846 // that the handle isn't empty before doing the checked cast.
847 if (!that.IsEmpty()) T::Cast(*that);
848#endif
849 return reinterpret_cast<Persistent<T>&>(const_cast<Persistent<S>&>(that));
850 }
851
852 // TODO(dcarney): this is pretty useless, fix or remove
853 template <class S>
854 V8_INLINE Persistent<S>& As() const { // NOLINT
855 return Persistent<S>::Cast(*this);
856 }
857
858 private:
859 friend class Isolate;
860 friend class Utils;
861 template<class F> friend class Local;
862 template<class F1, class F2> friend class Persistent;
863 template<class F> friend class ReturnValue;
864
865 explicit V8_INLINE Persistent(T* that) : PersistentBase<T>(that) {}
866 V8_INLINE T* operator*() const { return this->val_; }
867 template<class S, class M2>
868 V8_INLINE void Copy(const Persistent<S, M2>& that);
869};

877template <class T>
878class Global : public PersistentBase<T> {
879 public:
883 V8_INLINE Global() : PersistentBase<T>(nullptr) {}
889 template <class S>
890 V8_INLINE Global(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> that)
891 : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
892 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
893 }
899 template <class S>
900 V8_INLINE Global(Isolate* isolate, const PersistentBase<S>& that)
901 : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, that.val_)) {
902 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
903 }
907 V8_INLINE Global(Global&& other) : PersistentBase<T>(other.val_) { // NOLINT
908 other.val_ = nullptr;
909 }
910 V8_INLINE ~Global() { this->Reset(); }
914 template <class S>
915 V8_INLINE Global& operator=(Global<S>&& rhs) { // NOLINT
916 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
917 if (this != &rhs) {
918 this->Reset();
919 this->val_ = rhs.val_;
920 rhs.val_ = nullptr;
921 }
922 return *this;
923 }
927 Global Pass() { return static_cast<Global&&>(*this); } // NOLINT
928
929 /*
930 * For compatibility with Chromium's base::Bind (base::Passed).
931 */
932 typedef void MoveOnlyTypeForCPP03;
933
934 Global(const Global&) = delete;
935 void operator=(const Global&) = delete;
936
937 private:
938 template <class F>
939 friend class ReturnValue;
940 V8_INLINE T* operator*() const { return this->val_; }
941};

991 // Therefore declare them private instead to disable dynamic alloc
992 void* operator new(size_t size);
993 void* operator new[](size_t size);
994 void operator delete(void*, size_t);
995 void operator delete[](void*, size_t);
996
997 // Uses heap_object to obtain the current Isolate.
998 static internal::Object** CreateHandle(
999 internal::NeverReadOnlySpaceObject* heap_object, internal::Object* value);
1000
1001 internal::Isolate* isolate_;
1002 internal::Object** prev_next_;
1003 internal::Object** prev_limit_;
1004
1005 // Local::New uses CreateHandle with an Isolate* parameter.
1006 template<class F> friend class Local;
1007
1008 // Object::GetInternalField and Context::GetEmbedderData use CreateHandle with
1009 // a HeapObject* in their shortcuts.
1010 friend class Object;
1011 friend class Context;
1012};
1013

1019class V8_EXPORT EscapableHandleScope : public HandleScope {
1020 public:
1021 explicit EscapableHandleScope(Isolate* isolate);
1022 V8_INLINE ~EscapableHandleScope() {}
1023
1028 template <class T>
1029 V8_INLINE Local<T> Escape(Local<T> value) {
1030 internal::Object** slot =
1031 Escape(reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(*value));
1032 return Local<T>(reinterpret_cast<T*>(slot));
1033 }
1034
1035 template <class T>
1036 V8_INLINE MaybeLocal<T> EscapeMaybe(MaybeLocal<T> value) {
1037 return Escape(value.FromMaybe(Local<T>()));
1038 }
1039
1040 EscapableHandleScope(const EscapableHandleScope&) = delete;
1041 void operator=(const EscapableHandleScope&) = delete;
1042
1043 private:
1044 // Declaring operator new and delete as deleted is not spec compliant.
1045 // Therefore declare them private instead to disable dynamic alloc
1046 void* operator new(size_t size);
1047 void* operator new[](size_t size);
1048 void operator delete(void*, size_t);
1049 void operator delete[](void*, size_t);
1050
1051 internal::Object** Escape(internal::Object** escape_value);
1052 internal::Object** escape_slot_;
1053};

1137class ScriptOriginOptions {
1138 public:
1139 V8_INLINE ScriptOriginOptions(bool is_shared_cross_origin = false,
1140 bool is_opaque = false, bool is_wasm = false,
1141 bool is_module = false)
1142 : flags_((is_shared_cross_origin ? kIsSharedCrossOrigin : 0) |
1143 (is_wasm ? kIsWasm : 0) | (is_opaque ? kIsOpaque : 0) |
1144 (is_module ? kIsModule : 0)) {}
1145 V8_INLINE ScriptOriginOptions(int flags)
1146 : flags_(flags &
1147 (kIsSharedCrossOrigin | kIsOpaque | kIsWasm | kIsModule)) {}
1148
1149 bool IsSharedCrossOrigin() const {
1150 return (flags_ & kIsSharedCrossOrigin) != 0;
1151 }
1152 bool IsOpaque() const { return (flags_ & kIsOpaque) != 0; }
1153 bool IsWasm() const { return (flags_ & kIsWasm) != 0; }
1154 bool IsModule() const { return (flags_ & kIsModule) != 0; }
1155
1156 int Flags() const { return flags_; }
1157
1158 private:
1159 enum {
1160 kIsSharedCrossOrigin = 1,
1161 kIsOpaque = 1 << 1,
1162 kIsWasm = 1 << 2,
1163 kIsModule = 1 << 3
1164 };
1165 const int flags_;
1166};

1388class V8_EXPORT ScriptCompiler {
1389 public:
1397 struct V8_EXPORT CachedData {
1398 enum BufferPolicy {
1399 BufferNotOwned,
1400 BufferOwned
1401 };
1402
1403 CachedData()
1404 : data(NULL),
1405 length(0),
1406 rejected(false),
1407 buffer_policy(BufferNotOwned) {}
1408
1409 // If buffer_policy is BufferNotOwned, the caller keeps the ownership of
1410 // data and guarantees that it stays alive until the CachedData object is
1411 // destroyed. If the policy is BufferOwned, the given data will be deleted
1412 // (with delete[]) when the CachedData object is destroyed.
1413 CachedData(const uint8_t* data, int length,
1414 BufferPolicy buffer_policy = BufferNotOwned);
1415 ~CachedData();
1416 // TODO(marja): Async compilation; add constructors which take a callback
1417 // which will be called when V8 no longer needs the data.
1418 const uint8_t* data;
1419 int length;
1420 bool rejected;
1421 BufferPolicy buffer_policy;
1422
1423 // Prevent copying.
1424 CachedData(const CachedData&) = delete;
1425 CachedData& operator=(const CachedData&) = delete;
1426 };
1427

1432 public:

1437 CachedData* cached_data = NULL);
1438 V8_INLINE ~Source();
1439
1440 // Ownership of the CachedData or its buffers is *not* transferred to the
1441 // caller. The CachedData object is alive as long as the Source object is
1442 // alive.
1443 V8_INLINE const CachedData* GetCachedData() const;
1444
1445 V8_INLINE const ScriptOriginOptions& GetResourceOptions() const;
1446
1447 // Prevent copying.
1448 Source(const Source&) = delete;
1449 Source& operator=(const Source&) = delete;
1450
1451 private:

1957// A RegisterState represents the current state of registers used
1958// by the sampling profiler API.
1959struct RegisterState {

1962 void* sp; // Stack pointer.
1963 void* fp; // Frame pointer.
1964};

3866template<typename T>
3867class ReturnValue {
3868 public:
3869 template <class S> V8_INLINE ReturnValue(const ReturnValue<S>& that)
3870 : value_(that.value_) {
3871 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
3872 }
3873 // Local setters
3874 template <typename S>
3875 V8_INLINE V8_DEPRECATE_SOON("Use Global<> instead",
3876 void Set(const Persistent<S>& handle));
3877 template <typename S>
3878 V8_INLINE void Set(const Global<S>& handle);
3879 template <typename S>
3880 V8_INLINE void Set(const Local<S> handle);
3881 // Fast primitive setters
3882 V8_INLINE void Set(bool value);
3883 V8_INLINE void Set(double i);
3884 V8_INLINE void Set(int32_t i);
3885 V8_INLINE void Set(uint32_t i);
3886 // Fast JS primitive setters
3887 V8_INLINE void SetNull();
3888 V8_INLINE void SetUndefined();
3889 V8_INLINE void SetEmptyString();
3890 // Convenience getter for Isolate
3891 V8_INLINE Isolate* GetIsolate() const;
3892
3893 // Pointer setter: Uncompilable to prevent inadvertent misuse.
3894 template <typename S>
3895 V8_INLINE void Set(S* whatever);
3896
3897 // Getter. Creates a new Local<> so it comes with a certain performance
3898 // hit. If the ReturnValue was not yet set, this will return the undefined
3899 // value.
3900 V8_INLINE Local<Value> Get() const;
3901
3902 private:
3903 template<class F> friend class ReturnValue;
3904 template<class F> friend class FunctionCallbackInfo;
3905 template<class F> friend class PropertyCallbackInfo;
3906 template <class F, class G, class H>
3907 friend class PersistentValueMapBase;
3908 V8_INLINE void SetInternal(internal::Object* value) { *value_ = value; }
3909 V8_INLINE internal::Object* GetDefaultValue();
3910 V8_INLINE explicit ReturnValue(internal::Object** slot);
3911 internal::Object** value_;
3912};

6925struct JitCodeEvent {
6926 enum EventType {
6927 CODE_ADDED,
6928 CODE_MOVED,
6929 CODE_REMOVED,
6930 CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO,
6931 CODE_START_LINE_INFO_RECORDING,
6932 CODE_END_LINE_INFO_RECORDING
6933 };
6934 // Definition of the code position type. The "POSITION" type means the place
6935 // in the source code which are of interest when making stack traces to
6936 // pin-point the source location of a stack frame as close as possible.
6937 // The "STATEMENT_POSITION" means the place at the beginning of each
6938 // statement, and is used to indicate possible break locations.
6939 enum PositionType { POSITION, STATEMENT_POSITION };
6940
6941 // There are two different kinds of JitCodeEvents, one for JIT code generated
6942 // by the optimizing compiler, and one for byte code generated for the
6943 // interpreter. For JIT_CODE events, the |code_start| member of the event
6944 // points to the beginning of jitted assembly code, while for BYTE_CODE
6945 // events, |code_start| points to the first bytecode of the interpreted
6946 // function.
6947 enum CodeType { BYTE_CODE, JIT_CODE };
6948
6949 // Type of event.
6950 EventType type;
6951 CodeType code_type;
6952 // Start of the instructions.
6953 void* code_start;
6954 // Size of the instructions.
6955 size_t code_len;
6956 // Script info for CODE_ADDED event.
6957 Local<UnboundScript> script;
6958 // User-defined data for *_LINE_INFO_* event. It's used to hold the source
6959 // code line information which is returned from the
6960 // CODE_START_LINE_INFO_RECORDING event. And it's passed to subsequent
6961 // CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO and CODE_END_LINE_INFO_RECORDING events.
6962 void* user_data;
6963
6964 struct name_t {
6965 // Name of the object associated with the code, note that the string is not
6966 // zero-terminated.
6967 const char* str;
6968 // Number of chars in str.
6969 size_t len;
6970 };
6971
6972 struct line_info_t {
6973 // PC offset
6974 size_t offset;
6975 // Code position
6976 size_t pos;
6977 // The position type.
6978 PositionType position_type;
6979 };
6980
6981 union {
6982 // Only valid for CODE_ADDED.
6983 struct name_t name;
6984
6985 // Only valid for CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO
6986 struct line_info_t line_info;
6987
6988 // New location of instructions. Only valid for CODE_MOVED.
6989 void* new_code_start;
6990 };
6991
6992 Isolate* isolate;
6993};
6994
7000enum RAILMode {
7001 // Response performance mode: In this mode very low virtual machine latency
7002 // is provided. V8 will try to avoid JavaScript execution interruptions.
7003 // Throughput may be throttled.
7004 PERFORMANCE_RESPONSE,
7005 // Animation performance mode: In this mode low virtual machine latency is
7006 // provided. V8 will try to avoid as many JavaScript execution interruptions
7007 // as possible. Throughput may be throttled. This is the default mode.
7008 PERFORMANCE_ANIMATION,
7009 // Idle performance mode: The embedder is idle. V8 can complete deferred work
7010 // in this mode.
7011 PERFORMANCE_IDLE,
7012 // Load performance mode: In this mode high throughput is provided. V8 may
7013 // turn off latency optimizations.
7014 PERFORMANCE_LOAD
7015};
7016

8754template <class T>
8755class Maybe {
8756 public:
8757 V8_INLINE bool IsNothing() const { return !has_value_; }
8758 V8_INLINE bool IsJust() const { return has_value_; }
8759
8763 V8_INLINE T ToChecked() const { return FromJust(); }
8764
8769 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT V8_INLINE bool To(T* out) const {
8770 if (V8_LIKELY(IsJust())) *out = value_;
8771 return IsJust();
8772 }
8773
8778 V8_INLINE T FromJust() const {
8779 if (V8_UNLIKELY(!IsJust())) V8::FromJustIsNothing();
8780 return value_;
8781 }
8782
8787 V8_INLINE T FromMaybe(const T& default_value) const {
8788 return has_value_ ? value_ : default_value;
8789 }
8790
8791 V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Maybe& other) const {
8792 return (IsJust() == other.IsJust()) &&
8793 (!IsJust() || FromJust() == other.FromJust());
8794 }
8795
8796 V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Maybe& other) const {
8797 return !operator==(other);
8798 }
8799
8800 private:
8801 Maybe() : has_value_(false) {}
8802 explicit Maybe(const T& t) : has_value_(true), value_(t) {}
8803
8804 bool has_value_;
8805 T value_;
8806
8807 template <class U>
8808 friend Maybe<U> Nothing();
8809 template <class U>
8810 friend Maybe<U> Just(const U& u);
8811};
8812
8813template <class T>
8814inline Maybe<T> Nothing() {
8815 return Maybe<T>();
8816}
8817
8818template <class T>
8819inline Maybe<T> Just(const T& t) {
8820 return Maybe<T>(t);
8821}
8822
8823// A template specialization of Maybe<T> for the case of T = void.
8824template <>
8825class Maybe<void> {
8826 public:
8827 V8_INLINE bool IsNothing() const { return !is_valid_; }
8828 V8_INLINE bool IsJust() const { return is_valid_; }
8829
8830 V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Maybe& other) const {
8831 return IsJust() == other.IsJust();
8832 }
8833
8834 V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Maybe& other) const {
8835 return !operator==(other);
8836 }
8837
8838 private:
8839 struct JustTag {};
8840
8841 Maybe() : is_valid_(false) {}
8842 explicit Maybe(JustTag) : is_valid_(true) {}
8843
8844 bool is_valid_;
8845
8846 template <class U>
8847 friend Maybe<U> Nothing();
8848 friend Maybe<void> JustVoid();
8849};
8850
8851inline Maybe<void> JustVoid() { return Maybe<void>(Maybe<void>::JustTag()); }

9423class Internals {
9424 public:
9425 // These values match non-compiler-dependent values defined within
9426 // the implementation of v8.
9427 static const int kHeapObjectMapOffset = 0;
9428 static const int kMapInstanceTypeOffset = 1 * kApiPointerSize + kApiIntSize;
9429 static const int kStringResourceOffset = 3 * kApiPointerSize;
9430
9431 static const int kOddballKindOffset = 4 * kApiPointerSize + kApiDoubleSize;
9432 static const int kForeignAddressOffset = kApiPointerSize;
9433 static const int kJSObjectHeaderSize = 3 * kApiPointerSize;
9434 static const int kFixedArrayHeaderSize = 2 * kApiPointerSize;
9435 static const int kContextHeaderSize = 2 * kApiPointerSize;
9436 static const int kContextEmbedderDataIndex = 5;
9437 static const int kFullStringRepresentationMask = 0x0f;
9438 static const int kStringEncodingMask = 0x8;
9439 static const int kExternalTwoByteRepresentationTag = 0x02;
9440 static const int kExternalOneByteRepresentationTag = 0x0a;
9441
9442 static const int kIsolateEmbedderDataOffset = 0 * kApiPointerSize;
9443 static const int kExternalMemoryOffset = 4 * kApiPointerSize;
9444 static const int kExternalMemoryLimitOffset =
9445 kExternalMemoryOffset + kApiInt64Size;
9446 static const int kExternalMemoryAtLastMarkCompactOffset =
9447 kExternalMemoryLimitOffset + kApiInt64Size;
9448 static const int kIsolateRootsOffset = kExternalMemoryLimitOffset +
9449 kApiInt64Size + kApiInt64Size +
9450 kApiPointerSize + kApiPointerSize;
9451 static const int kUndefinedValueRootIndex = 4;
9452 static const int kTheHoleValueRootIndex = 5;
9453 static const int kNullValueRootIndex = 6;
9454 static const int kTrueValueRootIndex = 7;
9455 static const int kFalseValueRootIndex = 8;
9456 static const int kEmptyStringRootIndex = 9;
9457
9458 static const int kNodeClassIdOffset = 1 * kApiPointerSize;
9459 static const int kNodeFlagsOffset = 1 * kApiPointerSize + 3;
9460 static const int kNodeStateMask = 0x7;
9461 static const int kNodeStateIsWeakValue = 2;
9462 static const int kNodeStateIsPendingValue = 3;
9463 static const int kNodeStateIsNearDeathValue = 4;
9464 static const int kNodeIsIndependentShift = 3;
9465 static const int kNodeIsActiveShift = 4;
9466
9467 static const int kFirstNonstringType = 0x80;
9468 static const int kOddballType = 0x83;
9469 static const int kForeignType = 0x87;
9470 static const int kJSSpecialApiObjectType = 0x410;
9471 static const int kJSApiObjectType = 0x420;
9472 static const int kJSObjectType = 0x421;
9473
9474 static const int kUndefinedOddballKind = 5;
9475 static const int kNullOddballKind = 3;
9476
9477 static const uint32_t kNumIsolateDataSlots = 4;
9478
9479 V8_EXPORT static void CheckInitializedImpl(v8::Isolate* isolate);
9480 V8_INLINE static void CheckInitialized(v8::Isolate* isolate) {
9481#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
9482 CheckInitializedImpl(isolate);
9483#endif
9484 }
9485
9486 V8_INLINE static bool HasHeapObjectTag(const internal::Object* value) {
9487 return ((reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(value) & kHeapObjectTagMask) ==
9488 kHeapObjectTag);
9489 }
9490
9491 V8_INLINE static int SmiValue(const internal::Object* value) {
9492 return PlatformSmiTagging::SmiToInt(value);
9493 }
9494
9495 V8_INLINE static internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
9496 return PlatformSmiTagging::IntToSmi(value);
9497 }
9498
9499 V8_INLINE static bool IsValidSmi(intptr_t value) {
9500 return PlatformSmiTagging::IsValidSmi(value);
9501 }
9502
9503 V8_INLINE static int GetInstanceType(const internal::Object* obj) {
9504 typedef internal::Object O;
9505 O* map = ReadField<O*>(obj, kHeapObjectMapOffset);
9506 return ReadField<uint16_t>(map, kMapInstanceTypeOffset);
9507 }
9508
9509 V8_INLINE static int GetOddballKind(const internal::Object* obj) {
9510 typedef internal::Object O;
9511 return SmiValue(ReadField<O*>(obj, kOddballKindOffset));
9512 }
9513
9514 V8_INLINE static bool IsExternalTwoByteString(int instance_type) {
9515 int representation = (instance_type & kFullStringRepresentationMask);
9516 return representation == kExternalTwoByteRepresentationTag;
9517 }
9518
9519 V8_INLINE static uint8_t GetNodeFlag(internal::Object** obj, int shift) {
9520 uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(obj) + kNodeFlagsOffset;
9521 return *addr & static_cast<uint8_t>(1U << shift);
9522 }
9523
9524 V8_INLINE static void UpdateNodeFlag(internal::Object** obj,
9525 bool value, int shift) {
9526 uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(obj) + kNodeFlagsOffset;
9527 uint8_t mask = static_cast<uint8_t>(1U << shift);
9528 *addr = static_cast<uint8_t>((*addr & ~mask) | (value << shift));
9529 }
9530
9531 V8_INLINE static uint8_t GetNodeState(internal::Object** obj) {
9532 uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(obj) + kNodeFlagsOffset;
9533 return *addr & kNodeStateMask;
9534 }
9535
9536 V8_INLINE static void UpdateNodeState(internal::Object** obj,
9537 uint8_t value) {
9538 uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(obj) + kNodeFlagsOffset;
9539 *addr = static_cast<uint8_t>((*addr & ~kNodeStateMask) | value);
9540 }
9541
9542 V8_INLINE static void SetEmbedderData(v8::Isolate* isolate,
9543 uint32_t slot,
9544 void* data) {
9545 uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(isolate) +
9546 kIsolateEmbedderDataOffset + slot * kApiPointerSize;
9547 *reinterpret_cast<void**>(addr) = data;
9548 }
9549
9550 V8_INLINE static void* GetEmbedderData(const v8::Isolate* isolate,
9551 uint32_t slot) {
9552 const uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t*>(isolate) +
9553 kIsolateEmbedderDataOffset + slot * kApiPointerSize;
9554 return *reinterpret_cast<void* const*>(addr);
9555 }
9556
9557 V8_INLINE static internal::Object** GetRoot(v8::Isolate* isolate,
9558 int index) {
9559 uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(isolate) + kIsolateRootsOffset;
9560 return reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(addr + index * kApiPointerSize);
9561 }
9562
9563 template <typename T>
9564 V8_INLINE static T ReadField(const internal::Object* ptr, int offset) {
9565 const uint8_t* addr =
9566 reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t*>(ptr) + offset - kHeapObjectTag;
9567 return *reinterpret_cast<const T*>(addr);
9568 }
9569
9570 template <typename T>
9571 V8_INLINE static T ReadEmbedderData(const v8::Context* context, int index) {
9572 typedef internal::Object O;
9573 typedef internal::Internals I;
9574 O* ctx = *reinterpret_cast<O* const*>(context);
9575 int embedder_data_offset = I::kContextHeaderSize +
9576 (internal::kApiPointerSize * I::kContextEmbedderDataIndex);
9577 O* embedder_data = I::ReadField<O*>(ctx, embedder_data_offset);
9578 int value_offset =
9579 I::kFixedArrayHeaderSize + (internal::kApiPointerSize * index);
9580 return I::ReadField<T>(embedder_data, value_offset);
9581 }
9582};

9584// Only perform cast check for types derived from v8::Data since
9585// other types do not implement the Cast method.
9586template <bool PerformCheck>
9587struct CastCheck {
9588 template <class T>
9589 static void Perform(T* data);
9590};
9591
9592template <>
9593template <class T>
9594void CastCheck<true>::Perform(T* data) {
9595 T::Cast(data);
9596}
9597
9598template <>
9599template <class T>
9600void CastCheck<false>::Perform(T* data) {}
9601
9602template <class T>
9603V8_INLINE void PerformCastCheck(T* data) {
9604 CastCheck<std::is_base_of<Data, T>::value>::Perform(data);
9605}

9675template <class T, class M>
9676template <class S, class M2>
9677void Persistent<T, M>::Copy(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) {
9678 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
9679 this->Reset();
9680 if (that.IsEmpty()) return;
9681 internal::Object** p = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(that.val_);
9682 this->val_ = reinterpret_cast<T*>(V8::CopyPersistent(p));
9683 M::Copy(that, this);
9684}

9686template <class T>
9687bool PersistentBase<T>::IsIndependent() const {
9688 typedef internal::Internals I;
9689 if (this->IsEmpty()) return false;
9690 return I::GetNodeFlag(reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_),
9691 I::kNodeIsIndependentShift);
9692}
9693
9694template <class T>
9695bool PersistentBase<T>::IsNearDeath() const {
9696 typedef internal::Internals I;
9697 if (this->IsEmpty()) return false;
9698 uint8_t node_state =
9699 I::GetNodeState(reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_));
9700 return node_state == I::kNodeStateIsNearDeathValue ||
9701 node_state == I::kNodeStateIsPendingValue;
9702}
9703
9704
9705template <class T>
9706bool PersistentBase<T>::IsWeak() const {
9707 typedef internal::Internals I;
9708 if (this->IsEmpty()) return false;
9709 return I::GetNodeState(reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_)) ==
9710 I::kNodeStateIsWeakValue;
9711}

9718 val_ = 0;
9719}

9858template<typename T>
9859void ReturnValue<T>::Set(int32_t i) {
9860 TYPE_CHECK(T, Integer);
9861 typedef internal::Internals I;
9862 if (V8_LIKELY(I::IsValidSmi(i))) {
9863 *value_ = I::IntToSmi(i);
9864 return;
9865 }
9866 Set(Integer::New(GetIsolate(), i));
9867}
9868
9869template<typename T>
9870void ReturnValue<T>::Set(uint32_t i) {
9871 TYPE_CHECK(T, Integer);
9872 // Can't simply use INT32_MAX here for whatever reason.
9873 bool fits_into_int32_t = (i & (1U << 31)) == 0;
9874 if (V8_LIKELY(fits_into_int32_t)) {
9875 Set(static_cast<int32_t>(i));
9876 return;
9877 }
9878 Set(Integer::NewFromUnsigned(GetIsolate(), i));
9879}
9880
9881template<typename T>
9882void ReturnValue<T>::Set(bool value) {
9883 TYPE_CHECK(T, Boolean);
9884 typedef internal::Internals I;
9885 int root_index;
9886 if (value) {
9887 root_index = I::kTrueValueRootIndex;
9888 } else {
9889 root_index = I::kFalseValueRootIndex;
9890 }
9891 *value_ = *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), root_index);
9892}
9893
9894template<typename T>
9895void ReturnValue<T>::SetNull() {
9896 TYPE_CHECK(T, Primitive);
9897 typedef internal::Internals I;
9898 *value_ = *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), I::kNullValueRootIndex);
9899}

9901template<typename T>
9902void ReturnValue<T>::SetUndefined() {
9903 TYPE_CHECK(T, Primitive);
9904 typedef internal::Internals I;
9905 *value_ = *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), I::kUndefinedValueRootIndex);
9906}
9907
9908template<typename T>
9909void ReturnValue<T>::SetEmptyString() {
9910 TYPE_CHECK(T, String);
9911 typedef internal::Internals I;
9912 *value_ = *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), I::kEmptyStringRootIndex);
9913}

9915template <typename T>
9916Isolate* ReturnValue<T>::GetIsolate() const {
9917 // Isolate is always the pointer below the default value on the stack.
9918 return *reinterpret_cast<Isolate**>(&value_[-2]);
9919}
9920
9921template <typename T>
9922Local<Value> ReturnValue<T>::Get() const {
9923 typedef internal::Internals I;
9924 if (*value_ == *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), I::kTheHoleValueRootIndex))
9925 return Local<Value>(*Undefined(GetIsolate()));
9926 return Local<Value>::New(GetIsolate(), reinterpret_cast<Value*>(value_));
9927}

9933 TYPE_CHECK(S*, Primitive);
9934}

9936template<typename T>
9937internal::Object* ReturnValue<T>::GetDefaultValue() {
9938 // Default value is always the pointer below value_ on the stack.
9939 return value_[-1];
9940}
9941
9942template <typename T>
9943FunctionCallbackInfo<T>::FunctionCallbackInfo(internal::Object** implicit_args,
9944 internal::Object** values,
9945 int length)
9946 : implicit_args_(implicit_args), values_(values), length_(length) {}
9947
9948template<typename T>
9949Local<Value> FunctionCallbackInfo<T>::operator[](int i) const {
9950 if (i < 0 || length_ <= i) return Local<Value>(*Undefined(GetIsolate()));
9951 return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(values_ - i));
9952}
9953
9954
9955template<typename T>
9956Local<Object> FunctionCallbackInfo<T>::This() const {
9957 return Local<Object>(reinterpret_cast<Object*>(values_ + 1));
9958}
9959
9960
9961template<typename T>
9962Local<Object> FunctionCallbackInfo<T>::Holder() const {
9963 return Local<Object>(reinterpret_cast<Object*>(
9964 &implicit_args_[kHolderIndex]));
9965}
9966
9967template <typename T>
9968Local<Value> FunctionCallbackInfo<T>::NewTarget() const {
9969 return Local<Value>(
9970 reinterpret_cast<Value*>(&implicit_args_[kNewTargetIndex]));
9971}
9972
9973template <typename T>
9974Local<Value> FunctionCallbackInfo<T>::Data() const {
9975 return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(&implicit_args_[kDataIndex]));
9976}
9977
9978
9979template<typename T>
9980Isolate* FunctionCallbackInfo<T>::GetIsolate() const {
9981 return *reinterpret_cast<Isolate**>(&implicit_args_[kIsolateIndex]);
9982}
9983
9984
9985template<typename T>
9986ReturnValue<T> FunctionCallbackInfo<T>::GetReturnValue() const {
9987 return ReturnValue<T>(&implicit_args_[kReturnValueIndex]);
9988}
9989
9990
9991template<typename T>
9992bool FunctionCallbackInfo<T>::IsConstructCall() const {
9993 return !NewTarget()->IsUndefined();
9994}
9995
9996
9997template<typename T>
9998int FunctionCallbackInfo<T>::Length() const {
9999 return length_;
10000}

10112Local<Value> Object::GetInternalField(int index) {
10113#ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
10114 typedef internal::Object O;
10115 typedef internal::Internals I;
10116 O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O**>(this);
10117 // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
10118 // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
10119 auto instance_type = I::GetInstanceType(obj);
10120 if (instance_type == I::kJSObjectType ||
10121 instance_type == I::kJSApiObjectType ||
10122 instance_type == I::kJSSpecialApiObjectType) {
10123 int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (internal::kApiPointerSize * index);
10124 O* value = I::ReadField<O*>(obj, offset);
10125 O** result = HandleScope::CreateHandle(
10126 reinterpret_cast<internal::NeverReadOnlySpaceObject*>(obj), value);
10127 return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(result));
10128 }
10129#endif
10130 return SlowGetInternalField(index);
10131}
10132
10133
10134void* Object::GetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(int index) {
10135#ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
10136 typedef internal::Object O;
10137 typedef internal::Internals I;
10138 O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O**>(this);
10139 // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
10140 // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
10141 auto instance_type = I::GetInstanceType(obj);
10142 if (V8_LIKELY(instance_type == I::kJSObjectType ||
10143 instance_type == I::kJSApiObjectType ||
10144 instance_type == I::kJSSpecialApiObjectType)) {
10145 int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (internal::kApiPointerSize * index);
10146 return I::ReadField<void*>(obj, offset);
10147 }
10148#endif
10149 return SlowGetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(index);
10150}

10168
10169String::ExternalStringResource* String::GetExternalStringResource() const {
10170 typedef internal::Object O;
10171 typedef internal::Internals I;
10172 O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O* const*>(this);
10173 String::ExternalStringResource* result;
10174 if (I::IsExternalTwoByteString(I::GetInstanceType(obj))) {
10175 void* value = I::ReadField<void*>(obj, I::kStringResourceOffset);
10176 result = reinterpret_cast<String::ExternalStringResource*>(value);
10177 } else {
10178 result = NULL;
10179 }
10180#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
10181 VerifyExternalStringResource(result);
10182#endif
10183 return result;
10184}
10185
10186
10187String::ExternalStringResourceBase* String::GetExternalStringResourceBase(
10188 String::Encoding* encoding_out) const {
10189 typedef internal::Object O;
10190 typedef internal::Internals I;
10191 O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O* const*>(this);
10192 int type = I::GetInstanceType(obj) & I::kFullStringRepresentationMask;
10193 *encoding_out = static_cast<Encoding>(type & I::kStringEncodingMask);
10194 ExternalStringResourceBase* resource = NULL;
10195 if (type == I::kExternalOneByteRepresentationTag ||
10196 type == I::kExternalTwoByteRepresentationTag) {
10197 void* value = I::ReadField<void*>(obj, I::kStringResourceOffset);
10198 resource = static_cast<ExternalStringResourceBase*>(value);
10199 }
10200#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
10201 VerifyExternalStringResourceBase(resource, *encoding_out);
10202#endif
10203 return resource;
10204}

10210#else
10211 return QuickIsUndefined();
10212#endif
10213}
10214
10215bool Value::QuickIsUndefined() const {
10216 typedef internal::Object O;
10217 typedef internal::Internals I;
10218 O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O* const*>(this);
10219 if (!I::HasHeapObjectTag(obj)) return false;
10220 if (I::GetInstanceType(obj) != I::kOddballType) return false;
10221 return (I::GetOddballKind(obj) == I::kUndefinedOddballKind);
10222}

10228#else

10230#endif

10232
10233bool Value::QuickIsNull() const {
10234 typedef internal::Object O;
10235 typedef internal::Internals I;
10236 O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O* const*>(this);
10237 if (!I::HasHeapObjectTag(obj)) return false;
10238 if (I::GetInstanceType(obj) != I::kOddballType) return false;
10239 return (I::GetOddballKind(obj) == I::kNullOddballKind);
10240}

10242bool Value::IsNullOrUndefined() const {
10243#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
10244 return FullIsNull() || FullIsUndefined();
10245#else
10246 return QuickIsNullOrUndefined();
10247#endif
10248}
10249
10250bool Value::QuickIsNullOrUndefined() const {
10251 typedef internal::Object O;
10252 typedef internal::Internals I;
10253 O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O* const*>(this);
10254 if (!I::HasHeapObjectTag(obj)) return false;
10255 if (I::GetInstanceType(obj) != I::kOddballType) return false;
10256 int kind = I::GetOddballKind(obj);
10257 return kind == I::kNullOddballKind || kind == I::kUndefinedOddballKind;
10258}

10268bool Value::QuickIsString() const {

10270 typedef internal::Internals I;
10271 O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O* const*>(this);
10272 if (!I::HasHeapObjectTag(obj)) return false;
10273 return (I::GetInstanceType(obj) < I::kFirstNonstringType);
10274}

10704
10705void Isolate::SetData(uint32_t slot, void* data) {

10723MaybeLocal<T> Isolate::GetDataFromSnapshotOnce(size_t index) {

10728
10729int64_t Isolate::AdjustAmountOfExternalAllocatedMemory(
10730 int64_t change_in_bytes) {
10731 typedef internal::Internals I;
10732 const int64_t kMemoryReducerActivationLimit = 32 * 1024 * 1024;
10733 int64_t* external_memory = reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(
10734 reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) + I::kExternalMemoryOffset);
10735 int64_t* external_memory_limit = reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(
10736 reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) + I::kExternalMemoryLimitOffset);
10737 int64_t* external_memory_at_last_mc =
10738 reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) +
10739 I::kExternalMemoryAtLastMarkCompactOffset);
10740 const int64_t amount = *external_memory + change_in_bytes;
10741
10742 *external_memory = amount;
10743
10744 int64_t allocation_diff_since_last_mc =
10745 *external_memory_at_last_mc - *external_memory;
10746 allocation_diff_since_last_mc = allocation_diff_since_last_mc < 0
10747 ? -allocation_diff_since_last_mc
10748 : allocation_diff_since_last_mc;
10749 if (allocation_diff_since_last_mc > kMemoryReducerActivationLimit) {
10750 CheckMemoryPressure();
10751 }
10752
10753 if (change_in_bytes < 0) {
10754 *external_memory_limit += change_in_bytes;
10755 }
10756
10757 if (change_in_bytes > 0 && amount > *external_memory_limit) {
10758 ReportExternalAllocationLimitReached();
10759 }
10760 return *external_memory;
10761}
10762
10763Local<Value> Context::GetEmbedderData(int index) {
10764#ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
10765 typedef internal::Object O;
10766 typedef internal::Internals I;
10767 auto* context = *reinterpret_cast<internal::NeverReadOnlySpaceObject**>(this);
10768 O** result =
10769 HandleScope::CreateHandle(context, I::ReadEmbedderData<O*>(this, index));
10770 return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(result));
10771#else
10772 return SlowGetEmbedderData(index);
10773#endif
10774}
10775
10776
10777void* Context::GetAlignedPointerFromEmbedderData(int index) {
10778#ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
10779 typedef internal::Internals I;
10780 return I::ReadEmbedderData<void*>(this, index);
10781#else
10782 return SlowGetAlignedPointerFromEmbedderData(index);
10783#endif
10784}
